<br>
(also want fixed/replaced class RA, but am not sure the reflection one isn't too far over the top) <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://bellsouthpwp.net/d/o/donatea/x/sig-auren.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=t0a5t>t0a5t</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/18/03 4:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=509.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well..</span><hr size=1> You can't honestly begrudge the Minstrels their current good fortune. Granted it makes the well played chant twister Minstrel into a god character, but it also gives the majority who are average players a pretty decent character to play.<br>
<br>
On the Skald front, I do think a few tweaks are required. However, let me first say that Skald melee is fine. At 50 natural axe with buffs (getting to capped STR - and then some) I am usually flying with around 1500 weaponskill.<br>
<br>
Skald defense is basically non-existent much unlike the other music classes. <br>
<br>
Minstrels definitely have the best defense in terms of Stealth (can't kill what u can't see), Chain, Evade 2, Dodger, Small Shield, MoBlock, insta stun, AOE Mezz, Ablative Chant.<br>
<br>
Even Bards have better working defense in the form of Evade 2, insta AOE Mezz, castable Mezz and in the form of being a pure support class that stays out of melee range to do what it is best at - CC, end regen, healing.<br>
<br>
For a class that has to deal in wetworks, the skald has no working defense. First of all bugged Parry code renders parry useless for the most part. 700 range Mezz at it's current duration and 1500 range Snare is more an offensive tool useful for interruptions rather than defensive. Which leaves the skald with Evade 1/Chain as it's only reliable defense. <br>
<br>
So if we go about fixing defense, Evade 2 and access to Dodger would be a start. Other useful additions would be:<br>
<br>
- Increase range of Mezz to 1350 so we can start running if we see it get resisted.<br>
<br>
- PBAOE Insta Mezz.<br>
<br>
- Increase Snare Strength with higher levels so that at level 41 it snares 80% or so.<br>
<br>
Then we need to re-evaluate whether you want the class as a frontliner, or a support character. Being based off the viking class, it is highly unlikely that the class will get the level of support utility that Minstrels and Bards get. At that juncture, you might wish to compare yourself to the Paladin for the type of 'utility' Mythic designates for melee based classes.<br>
<br>
- 2000 unit Damage Add Chant is a neccessity.<br>
<br>
- Consolidated Resist Chants with 2000 range are another neccessity.<br>
<br>
- Some additional chant that we can play in combat if there is a Runemaster in the group to provide Damage Adds.<br>
<br>
Then we need to address RAs since Mythic considers this the universal balancer - the great equalizer between classes and realms.<br>
<br>
- The biggest blow to Skalds and the entire notion of Front Loaded damage has been the introduction of IP. To destroy balance further, when a fully buffed tank IPs, it heals them for over 2300 hitpoints. A fully buffed Skald IPs and they only get a 1900 HP heal out of it. Yet it costs 23 RSPs for a Skald to get it and only 17 RSPs for a pure tank. We pay more to get it and it still does less for us than those who pay less for it.<br>
I propose a RA for hybrids that let us use all our RAs more frequently. That way if we pay more for Purge/AP/IP, with our hybrid specific RA, we can half the timer for reusing them. Let our RSPs actually bring us some kind of return in investment.<br>
<br>
- We need a class specific RA that actually benefits an entire group. Perhaps a Dispel Magic chant that for the duration of effect any hit from your group has a chance of Dispelling all random beneficial effect from the enemy target. Or a Purge type RA that reduces negative effects on the group and reduces their duration - not only would it work on DOTs, debuffs, etc, but also on Mezzes - so you could effectively hit it when you think your group will get Mezzed (1850 range soon from sorcs btw) and by the time your enemy comes into range, your chant has purged the negative Mezz effects. Whatever it is, it needs to be on the same level as SoS, BoF, BAoD or Group Purge.<br>
<br>
I honestly don't think any and all of what I have suggested would even come close to overpowering the class, and if you do think so, please let me know why.<br>
<br>
