<br>
Just one comment :<br>
&quot; Being based off the viking class, it is highly unlikely that the class will get the level of support utility that Minstrels and Bards get &quot;<br>
The paradox here is that the base class doesn't mean anything past the 5 first levels. The only thing skalds get for beeing a viking is speccable parry.<br>
Currently, there are caster weaponskills and hp tables, pure melee tables, and for the rest of the classes, minimal differences. This is a completely illogical system, the differences are blurred. <br>
All hybrid classes that come from the fighter/viking/guardian base class should be on a table that is significantly more favorable than &quot;thieves&quot; or &quot;priests&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=t0a5t>t0a5t</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/18/03 5:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=509.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> absolutely</span><hr size=1> &quot;All hybrid classes that come from the fighter/viking/guardian base class should be on a table that is significantly more favorable than &quot;thieves&quot; or &quot;priests&quot;.&quot;<br>
